reviewText: Despite being almost 50 years old, this series hasn't dated as badly as some. It's a spoof of James Bond, a showcase for 1960's fashions and it has Patrick McNee and Diana Rigg at their best. We won't see their like again.

The VHS tape played well and I don't remember ever having seen 50,000 Breakfast. I don't think the last few '67 shows were as well made but I still enjoyed the interaction between the actors. Too bad Diana Rigg left. She has a real presence on screen.
